Sentencas: In symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells, comprehensively understanding the elementary reaction processes and the polarization behaviors of redox-stable electrode materials is critical for further optimization of the electrode performance.
Titulo: A practical approach for identifying various polarization behaviors of redox-stable electrodes in symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, a systematical and practical approach, based on electrochemical impedance spectroscopy technology, is applied to identify the rate-limiting elementary reactions of the redox-stable electrodes.
Titulo: A practical approach for identifying various polarization behaviors of redox-stable electrodes in symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The feasibility of this proposed method is demonstrated in symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-sigma-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 as electrodes.
Titulo: A practical approach for identifying various polarization behaviors of redox-stable electrodes in symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Based on the characteristic frequency ranges and the experimental results tested under various fuel gas components, operating temperatures, and discharge current densities, the rate-limiting steps of the cathode are associated with the formation of adsorbed oxygen ions and the combination of oxygen ions and oxygen vacancies, while the rate limiting steps of the anode are ascribed to the hydrogen dissociated adsorption and the steam desorption processes.
Titulo: A practical approach for identifying various polarization behaviors of redox-stable electrodes in symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This experimental and analysis framework can be straightforwardly extended to other electrode materials to unravel their electrochemical performance in detail.
Titulo: A practical approach for identifying various polarization behaviors of redox-stable electrodes in symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells
